"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Kappacasein is an amazing food stand right at the end of a row of great lunch choices at Borough Market. You&#39;ll be tempted by all the other offerings, but I implore you to pass them up at least once for that toasted cheese sandwich. After one taste, you&#39;ll probably pass them all up again, and again, and again.<br><br>The queue starts up after 11/12, but since I&#39;ve become very lucky in living close to Borough Market I&#39;ve taken to coming around 10:30 and making a brunch out of it. Believe me when I say you won&#39;t need much more until dinner time! And that way I only ever wait about 5 minutes for my gooey goodness.<br><br>The bread is toasted to PERFECTION, and the cheese is perfectly melted, even some of the cheese on the outside becomes nice and crunchy and beautiful without being burnt whilst everything on the inside is gooey and irresistible. The addition of onions and leeks makes it really special without taking the focus away from the cheese. I sometimes find myself feeling like I&#39;m intoxicated by cheesey goodness, just comfort food at it&#39;s best. For a fiver, you really cannot go wrong.",
