"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I LOVE this place, and as I can see, I am definitely not the only one!<br><br>Japanese Centre is just beetween the Japanese mall and the japanese restaurant Toku (which by the way belongs to Japanese centre)<br><br>One of the biggest japanese shop in London. The products quality is great, it&#39;s japanese after all, <br>The shop is divided in two parts, the store which sells great japanese imported products, and the little restaurant. It&#39;s very small, and there are not much seatings, but the food is good. You can just by some fresh sushis or sashimis on the stands and eat in.<br><br>What&#39;s not to be missed : If you want to eat in and order some noodles at the restaurant, ask for the udon there are just amazing! *slurp* <br><br>Money, money, money : The sushis/sashimis are around £3-£5 for 3 to 6 pieces. <br>The prices of the products in the store are not cheap, as it&#39;s all imported.  <br><br>That little thing : First of all, i have to say that the cashiers are really efficient. Sometimes the line may seems very long, but the wait is not. <br>A big thanks to the cashiers for they efficiency and courtesy <br>A little plus for the fresh daily sushi and bakery<br><br>What needs to be work on : Let me think about it... that&#39;s it! what&#39;s really missing is japanese ice cream! you can find some sweet desserts in the bakery and frozen stands, but nothing beat some real authentic japanese ice cream! taro, red bean flavour !",
