"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/vqxMyvegKbOG8IYuXHDNhg/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I only discovered the Carpenter&#39;s a few weeks ago but it&#39;s become my new favourite and here&#39;s why.<br><br>It&#39;s a proper pub where everything is just right. Well chosen beer selection (not too many, I don&#39;t need hundreds of choices). The staff are friendly and you get the feeling they take pride in their pub.<br><br>The pub itself is just what I want in a pub. Not too big, not to small and with cosy tables to sit at in a dark wood interior. There are several rooms extending to the back and and even a tiny beer garden hidden away behind that. It&#39;s a pleasant contrast to those wannabe &#39;gastro&#39; places with huge huge dining room tables with deafening volume that require to you shout across to be heard. None of that here. It&#39;s all on a more human scale.<br><br>It&#39;s another example of my personal rule that says that the best pubs in London are just far enough off the beaten track...not outside a tube station or directly on a crowded thoroughfare but slightly hidden away. In this case it&#39;s about a 5 minute walk down a quiet street from the seething crowds in the Brick Lane area. This is where they always are...<br><br>That also means that the punters are pleasant and not full of irritating types and you don&#39;t need to push through crowds to get served.<br><br>Haven&#39;t tried the food but it fits with the rest of the pub, the menu at least is proper pub food, refreshingly absent of silly named dishes desperately trying to be on trend.<br><br>Just perfect.",
