"reviewcomment":"Apart from HKK, this is, I think, in terms of food quality the best Chinese restaurant in London. When you consider that it costs slightly under half what you&#39;d pay at HKK it is absolutely fantastic value. <br><br>Chef Peng has now relinquished control of the dining room to his son but remains in the kitchen churning out delicious dishes I&#39;ve never seen on a menu, and owing to the fact that Hunan doesn&#39;t have a menu, I probably never will. It&#39;s best with about 8 people so they can bring out lots of small dishes. Dishes come out of the kitchen at a relaxed pace, once you say you are full to bursting they bring out some fritters and you are done.<br><br>The food is at a flat rate. I think it was around £45 last time I went so it&#39;s not your local takeaway but it is 100% worth the money. Their wine list is excellent too, go for an Alsatian varietal and you can&#39;t go too far wrong. Have a little lychee wine as a digestif and you will be good to go.",
