"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Can someone please just start up a charity for me to have breakfast/brunch here every morning? It would be ever so greatly appreciated. <br><br>For real though- this place does an incredible breakfast/brunch, and somehow, although I hear horror stories galore about having to wait ages for a table (at The Table, ha! aren&#39;t they so witty!), every time I&#39;ve come, the wait has been either non-existent or minimal. Which thank god, because I don&#39;t know how long I could wait to get my hands on their insane poached eggs and waffles! <br><br>Although I&#39;ve never tried their meat-based breakfast options, many brunching companions have, and all can testify to their goodness (honestly, seeing their Full Borough breakfast, I have, on occasion doubted my choice of vegetarian-ness). In addition, they do great lunch burgers and their fixed lunch is fabulous (although, with the fixed menu, it can be a little hit-and-miss if they happen to be serving something you don&#39;t particularly like). <br><br>A particularly positive point of The Table&#39;s, is that when you order tea, instead of just bringing you a cup of tea, as most places tend to do, they bring you an entire pot of it (it helps that their pot is nice as well... what doesn&#39;t this place get right?)! But, if you&#39;re not a tea fan, don&#39;t worry- everything else is good too!",
