"reviewcomment":"What a lovely meal we had at Santore... We ventured out to the adorable Exmouth Market to celebrate. Chris F. and I are always bookmarking places for special date nights&#39; and he planned this one, but coincidentally, I also had this gem bookmarked. <br><br>We started with the soup of the day - Creamy Chickpea Potato. This has to be one of the most lovely soups I&#39;ve ever had. It came with lovely pieces of bread on top. Perfectly seasoned. Yum!<br><br>My husband ordered the Vegetarian pizza and I ordered the folded pizza, which was like an Italian quesadilla. Delicious. Though Chris&#39; pizza was nice, mine was divine, and I had so much left-over that we were able to eat it the next day for the majority of our lunchtime meal.<br><br>Santore adds a 12.5% service charge, but as an American, I&#39;m good with tipping, and usually leave more than 12.5% anyway.<br><br>The wait staff was very nice. We had a lovely meal and lovely time at Santore. I can&#39;t wait to go back. The only thing I would have done differently would have been to order extra soups to go for the next day. That soup was so darn good!",
