"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"We came on a weekday for an early dinner so mostly enjoyed the pre-theatre deal of two courses for £15 (done between 5:30pm and 7:30pm).   The pre-theatre is good value considering it included most of the mains which cost about that on their own.  The service was great and the food was delicious.  They also obliged us with the free glass of bubbly with the yelp check-in deal.  <br><br>I originally found this place while googling around for a good English Gastropub to take some out of town visitors but I wouldn&#39;t really say this is a pub.  It&#39;s more of a chic rustic English restaurant with amazing locally sourced fare.  <br><br>Starters:<br>squash soup  - ehh.. it was ok.  I had to add salt pepper which is a bad sign..<br>rare beef, rocket &amp; horseradish  -  pretty good<br>Yorkshire wild rabbit, foie gras &amp; raisin bread terrine - loved it<br><br>Mains<br>Mount Grace farm British Lop port chip, English mustard cream - loved it<br>Wild black bream fillet, cauliflower puree - loved it<br>white park bavette steak with chips - loved it (and finally some good chips!  the right combo of crispy on the outside, delish on the inside)<br><br>The menu changes frequently (maybe even weekly) so take the above as indication of style you&#39;re likely to see.<br><br>A few miscellaneous items:<br>They advertised a brunch but it doesn&#39;t seem to be american style -- i&#39;ll have to give it a go and update this review later.   The server said they served a mean bloody mary.   We shall see..<br>I also noticed a side room which would be perfect for a party!  They had it set up with a large feasting table at the window facing the street and to the back a nice leather couch and seating for a cocktail area.  I can imagine a small engagement party, rehearsal dinner or our sad so say leaving London party I&#39;ve yet to plan..<br><br>Enjoy!",
