"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Definitely the best Indian in/around Upper Street.<br><br>I&#39;m not the best person to rate Indian restaurants as I don&#39;t like very spicy food, but that does mean that I often eat dishes which are a bit more subtle which don&#39;t respond to the approach of sticking in enough chillies  and hoping that no-one notices...<br><br>Zaffrani&#39;s milder dishes are not bland at all, they&#39;re subtly spiced and don&#39;t make you feel like you&#39;re eating a warm yoghurt while everyone around you is having spicy fun.  I&#39;m a particular fan of the biryanis which come in either mild or spicy varieties of chicken or lamb which is a really tasty, interesting meal with great veg curry sauce.<br><br>My friends who eat the hotter stuff also love the place and comment that the you taste flavours and not just red sauce...<br><br>Service is friendly and efficient, the place is packed quite tightly but never gets too loud or feels cramped... I&#39;ve eaten here a lot and will continue to do so!",
