"reviewcomment":"Honestly in a city ravaged by chain pubs, the Marquis of Cornwallis offers a very high class environment while seemingly avoiding the chain-tag. Though I am never surprised to find out something is a chain, this doesn&#39;t appear to be one.<br><br>This pub doesn&#39;t have the greatest prices in this century, but is a good place to grab one pint. Food prices hover around the 10+ pound range so again, this isn&#39;t a cheap place, but is is quite nice! Coming in here for a pint or two is all I&#39;d recommend if you are on a budget.<br><br>The seating is extremely comfortable and the pub is very spacious, including a second level. It has a wholesome feel and is very very clean. Staff is semi-eager to usher you out after you&#39;ve finished your pint, but they won&#39;t do anything about it if you sit around talking.<br><br>The selection of beers on tap is another plus; there are several microbrews and the standard mainstream beers. It&#39;s worth trying something new at this place, the local taps are tasty as hell!! (is hell tasty?)<br><br>Overall, this place is a grand slam (baseball reference). A true touchdown (american football reference) of the sphere of pubs in London. Honestly, it&#39;s a slam dunk (basketball reference). <br><br>Hole in one (golf).",
