"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/iEutDP0agSpVsNT5DBnvjg/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I asked my hotel manager for a casual place to eat that was not a chain thinking he was going to tell me to go to Mc Donalds.  Well...he told me to go to Pret a Manger ...while is a chain...he said there food is very good and they give anything they don&#39;t sell at the end of the day to the homeless...sounds cool.<br><br>You go in and there are open refrigerators that have all different kinds of sandwiches mostly baguette. At lunch, they have hot wraps too.  You bring your selection to the counter where you can also purchase soup, coffee, or tea.  They have a take away and eat in price.  The price to take it away is about 50 pence less per item than eating in.   Genius!!   I never had to find a table even during the busy lunch hour...<br><br>I had the Thai Chili Chicken which was delish...  It&#39;s like chicken salad with Sweet Thai Chili sauce.  The baguette that the chicken is housed in is VERY fresh and with a slight crisp outside.  It really reminded me of a Banh Mi.  The price was under 3 pounds.  <br><br>They also make yummy breakfast baguettes.  I had the egg and bacon.  And the egg is basically egg salad.  Thought that was weird but it tasted pretty good.   One morning I did stop in hoping to grab some lunch stuff for an all day bus tour but they don&#39;t sell the lunch till later...<br><br>A few days into my London trip, and I realize this place is like Starbucks is to Seattle.  You will not have trouble finding one or several in close proximity. <br><br>They are all about using local in season ingredients, they donate to the homeless and they are OCD about recycling (will see signs on the wall everywhere).  Really wish there was one of these in the US.  Highly recommend!!  Well ..not really because you&#39;ll probably end up there anyways...lol.",
