"reviewcomment":"Andrew Edmunds is a quaint European restaurant in SoHo in London. I had heard of Andrew Edmunds from friends before and it is quite highly rated on Zagat so decided to book dinner for a friend that had just moved to London that evening. When we arrived at Andrew Edmunds, we were surprised to see that the restaurant is around 8 tables or so that are closely packed (reminded me quite a lot of a small restaurant in Southern France). The decor is quite romantic with used wine bottles corked with candles burning on the table, a chalk board with up to date wine specials, and a handwritten menu. The wine list is phenomenal - they source their wine list from high-end retailers in London and buy the last few bottles of a bin at a significant discount. They truly pass along the discount to the costumer - bottles begin around £18 for their house red Corbieres and upward to hundreds of pounds for known vintages of French, Italian, Spanish, Australian, and Napa/Sonoma wines. The menu is filled with classically French and British dishes that are simple but well crafted. We decided on the winter stew, lemon sole, and lentil and aubergine for the three mains, along with the charcuterie for an appetizer, and the cheese plate for dessert. The Corbieres was splendid (and reasonably priced) and the mains were surprising great (plus, the price point was from £12.50 for the lentils to £22 for the sole, so quite reasonable for SoHo). The cheese dish was sourced from local farms outside of London and was one of the nicest cheese plates I have had in a long time. As an aside, Andrew Edmunds does not do online reservations and does not accept them more than a week in advance. Calling for reservations 3 or more days in advance is quite recommended in order to get a spot (especially for the weekends). The staff were attentive and helpful in selecting a dish, but were also not too hovering, so we felt we could sit for as long after our meal as we wished. The dishes were also well-timed, so courses did not overlap. Overall, Andrew Edmunds was a splendid restaurant. If you are looking for a higher end French/European restaurant to take a date or to catch up with good friends, Andrew Edmunds is a great choice.",
