"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Yg93P_JyxHsN65lOTU7CNg/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Again, this review is just for the downstairs bar. <br><br>Atmosphere:<br><br>Almost indescribably chill vibe. As you walk in you&#39;re greeted by the sight of 5-6 really comfy couches, really chill music in the background, and anime being screened on one of the walls. Though we went at 2030 on a Friday, there were maybe 2 other groups, and 5 of us were able to get a seat. There&#39;s just something about the bar that makes it feel like you&#39;re in a secret spot that no one else knows about.<br><br>Drinks:<br><br>Pretty decent selection. 4 types of sake, 3 types of shochu, and around 12 sake and shochu based cocktails. Beyond that there&#39;s the usual selection of liquor you&#39;d expect to find in a bar. Prices are really reasonable too! They have Asahi on tap for £4, and the house sake starts at £4 as well. I only tried the 2 types of sake that the bartender said were slightly sweeter, but really enjoyed both (though I wish they had a larger selection).<br><br>post-10pm:<br><br>Around 2145 we contemplated moving somewhere else as the vibe was almost too chill for a Friday. However at 10 the staff informed us that they had to move all the furniture out of the way. So they cleared the floor, a dj showed up, the music went up just a tiny bit and from being a quiet spot, by around 2230 there were probably 40 people there. <br><br>It has to be said that I still left at 2300 but it really was the perfect place to start the night. Food wise I only tried the edamame which was good but after reading the reviews i&#39;ll be sure to try other nibbles as well next time.",
