"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/UOEE2eS_MXAMEZcdII6TvA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Food is no-frills Italian fare, served up with a warm smile and hot from the kitchen located at the heart of this small restaurant where you can watch your server running in and out and helping to happily prepare your food.<br><br>The minute I walked through the door, I had a feeling of familiarity and comfort like going to a place where they know you and treat you like family. And with that family environment in mind, this place does not worry about primping their food or table setting - There are no trendy spins on recipes, no hip interior décor or polished wait staff - This is simple, honest Italian food and friendly service.<br><br>What I tried: Insalata Tricolore, Bruchetta, Garlic Bread, Spaghetti Bolognese, Lasagna Della Casa (my husband ordered the lasagna and I had a bite - wowie I&#39;d order this next time!) and a couple bottles of Chianti. I can&#39;t say this is the best Italian food I&#39;ve ever had, but it&#39;s one of the best food experiences in London for a taste from Nonni&#39;s kitchen (or Nonno/Pappi in this case, since there are only blokes running the place from what I could see). Go and enjoy - Buon appetito!",
