"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/aCdYdkylhHmzi9PONKsMkA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"The halibut is not laughing, he&#39;s dead, fried, &amp; delicious. <br><br>You know it&#39;s good when the Coffee place next door has a sign in front to not form a queue to block their entrance.  As a novice, I formed the queue not realizing that you can just go directly inside if you are not doing take away. My bad. <br><br>Our friendly server recommended the haddock and cod. The women working here are awesome. Efficient and willing to cover each other to meet needs of the dining area. Genuinely smiling and hospitable. <br><br>Fish was hot and crispy and once I squeezed the lemon wedge across the fish, our family dove right in. Mushy peas and gravy seemed to be a traditional favorite here so I jumped on that band wagon and added it to our Friday Fish Fry. I loved dipping my chips in the gravy which was thick and savory. <br><br>Great place for the best fish and chips in London, if you are like me checking off a foodie list.",
