"reviewcomment":"I think this is by far one of my favorite restaurants in 2012.<br>The food: AMAZING!!! Highly recommend their Steak and Mushroom pie (see photo). The pie is just thin enough to get that buttery taste and the cruchness, but not too much to feel that&#39;s all you are getting of the pie; the sauce is rich and creamy; the steak is so tender and soft that they almost melt in your mouth... <br>I think it&#39;s one of The Best I have ever had, it is certainly to die for. All the other food are very good quality too (i.e. the Tuna starter - who says you can&#39;t get fresh sea food in London?)<br>The atmosphere: I have been here during lunch as well as dinner, both occasions it was busy but not TOO busy allowing you to fully enjoy the atmosphere and the food. The decoration of the restaurant gives a clean nice vintage feel, mixing it with the traditional British cuisine.<br>Price: considering it is in the middle of Mayfair and the quality of the restaurant, the price is very reasonable! The main courses are in average £10-15. If you order a main and a drink only, you can easily walk out with just paying £15 (say you order the pie and a soft drink) <br>The staff are young and trendy (and incidentally good looking!) but also friendly and attentive.<br><br>Try this place guys! Thumb up!",
