"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"All I wanted to eat in London was fish and chips and I searched Yelp for &#34;the best&#34; and in between stops at pubs, some rocking fish and chips would surely hit the spot.  We sought out Rock and Sole Plaice and this &#34;no frills&#34; fish and chips place dates back to 1871 and serves fish of your choice fried up with chips and other offered sides if you choose.  Portions are pretty big and cheaper to order to go but given that it was a cold november night, boyfriend and I opted to dine in, ordered a large cod fish and chips to share along with beers and tea for me.  Service was friendly, efficient and unobtrusive. Our cod was fresh and fried perfectly golden and crispy on the outside, moist and flaky on the inside and not too heavy and greasy at all accompanied by lemon and tartar sauce and accompanied chips were tasty as well.  I wanted to try their famed mushy peas but was too full, next time!<br><br>Joanna&#39;s mission to eat some good fish and chips accomplished!",
