"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"This is a review of their afternoon tea. I&#39;ve never stayed in the hotel because I live here, but the pictures sure look nice! I&#39;ve had afternoon tea here, twice. If it&#39;s warm out, you&#39;ll want to see if you can sit on the terrace overlooking their garden, because, well, that is awesome. You sit there the whole time thinking, &#34;Wow, it&#39;s warm in London.&#34; If not, they have a lovely indoor dining room. Be sure to call in advance, especially if you&#39;re going there during the weekend, because it often fills up.<br><br>With the afternoon team, do come hungry. (Is that not a classy thing to say?) And be sure to wear something nice -- jeans and a t-shirt will probably make you feel out of place. Then you&#39;ll enjoy the usual assortment of sandwiches (crust cut off!), scones (clotted cream piled on), and mini desserts. Most people end up ordering their house tea, which is very good, and you can also opt to add champagne.<br><br>Gluten-free notes: Yes, they do gluten-free afternoon tea. It&#39;s best to call them in advance and let them know, and confirm that they&#39;ll have scones and sandwiches for you. Then you can eat just like everybody else. Amazing! Clotted cream is naturally gluten-free, by the way. London is great for gluten-free eaters.",
